## 2. How to Publish (The Easy Way: Vercel)

Since you are using Next.js, **Vercel** is the best platform. It is free for personal projects and handles everything automatically.

### Step 1: Create a GitHub Repository
1.  Go to [github.com/new](https://github.com/new).
2.  Name it (e.g., `my-portfolio`).
3.  Do **not** check "Initialize with README" (you already have code).
4.  Click "Create repository".

### Step 2: Push your code
Run these commands in your VSCode terminal:

```powershell
# Initialize git if you haven't (I see a .git folder, so you might just need to add remote)
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/my-portfolio.git
git branch -M main
git add .
git commit -m "Initial launch"
git push -u origin main
```

### Step 3: Connect to Vercel
1.  Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) and sign up with **GitHub**.
2.  Click **"Add New..."** -> **"Project"**.
3.  You will see your `my-portfolio` repository. Click **Import**.
4.  Click **Deploy**.

**That's it!** Vercel will give you a live URL.

